Basic structure of HTML
declaration - it tells the type and version of the doc to the browser
<!DOCTYPE html>
these acts as root elements
<html> 
    head is used to define the title , meta data and third party 
    <head>
        <title> html page </title>

    </head>
    <body>
        this is where we write the actual content of the page
    </body>
</html>
